contrast,user experience	Defects
Selling Point
Defects and Selling Points both originate from real user experiences but represent contrasting aspects of product evaluation.

fast return on investment,investment return,recommendation	Honda Wave 110i
Rider Delivery
Honda Wave 110i is recommended for Rider Delivery due to its fast return on investment.

budget friendly,design appeal	University Student
Yamaha Fazzio
Yamaha Fazzio is suggested for University Students on a budget or those seeking a cute design.<SEP>Yamaha Fazzio is suggested for University Students who want a budget-friendly and appealing design.

PCX 160 is suggested for Office Workers as it provides comfort and efficient commuting over longer distances.<SEP>PCX 160 is recommended for Office Workers due to its comfort and efficient commuting over longer distances.

durability,recommendation	Rider Delivery
Yamaha Finn
Yamaha Finn is suggested for Rider Delivery because it has a 5-year warranty and can withstand rough usage.

budget friendly,design appeal	Grand Filano
University Student
Grand Filano is another option for University Students who want to save money or prefer a cute design.

performance in poor conditions,water capability	Heavy Duty/Flooded Area
Honda ADV 160
Honda ADV 160 is suggested for areas with poor road conditions or frequent flooding due to its robust suspension and deep water capability.

maneuverability,time efficiency	NMAX 155
Office Worker
NMAX 155 is recommended for Office Workers due to its ease of maneuvering and efficient travel times.

safety improvement	125cc Scooter Upgrade
Active Safety
The concept of Active Safety is highlighted when upgrading from a 125cc scooter to a 160cc scooter, emphasizing enhanced safety during acceleration and overtaking.

ride quality improvement	ADV Scooters
Showa Suspension
Showa Suspension enhances the ride quality of ADV scooters by providing a smoother experience.

comfort recommendation,storage convenience	Honda Lead 125
Rider Delivery
Honda Lead 125 is recommended for Rider Delivery who prefer comfort due to its ease of storage and quick fueling.

performance recommendation	Honda Giorno+
University Student
Honda Giorno+ is recommended for University Students looking for performance.

equipment provision,performance enhancement	Honda Forza 350
Showa
Showa provides rear shock absorbers with sub-tanks that enhance Honda Forza 350's performance.

collaboration,development partnership,engine development	GPX Drone 150
SYM
SYM collaborates with the manufacturer of GPX Drone 150 for engine development.<SEP>GPX Drone 150 is developed in collaboration with SYM.

storage capacity upgrade	NMAX 155
XMAX 160
The storage space under the seat in XMAX 160 is larger compared to NMAX 155, allowing for two helmet storage instead of one.

engineering feature,stability improvement	Dual Clamp Front Fork
Yamaha XMAX 300
The Yamaha XMAX 300 is equipped with dual clamp front forks for improved handling and stability.

clutch technology,performance enhancement,safety feature	Assist & Slipper Clutch
Yamaha R15M
The Yamaha R15M features an assist and slipper clutch to prevent rear wheel lock-up during downshifts.<SEP>Yamaha R15M includes an assist and slipper clutch for smoother downshifts and less aggressive clutch engagement.

convenience,feature integration	Electric Windshield
Honda Forza 350
The Honda Forza 350 integrates an electric windshield that can be adjusted up to 180 mm.

market competitor,price comparison	GPX Drone 150
PCX
GPX Drone 150 competes with PCX in terms of market positioning and pricing.

performance and stability upgrade	NMAX 155
PCX 160
The transition from PCX 160 to ADV emphasizes improved suspension quality and safety in rough conditions.

clutch technology,safety feature	Assist & Slipper Clutch
MT-15
The MT-15 is equipped with an assist and slipper clutch for smoother gear shifts and enhanced safety.

common defect,maintenance issue	Clutch Noise
Honda Forza 350
Honda Forza 350 often experiences clutch noise and vibration as a common defect.

common defect,maintenance issue	Oil Consumption
Yamaha XMAX 300
Yamaha XMAX 300 experiences oil consumption as a common defect requiring frequent checks.

market competitor,price comparison	GPX Drone 150
NMAX
GPX Drone 150 competes with NMAX in terms of market positioning and pricing.

convenience,feature integration,performance improvement,user convenience	Quick Shifter
Yamaha R15M
The Yamaha R15M integrates a quick shifter feature allowing gear changes without clutch use (on some models).<SEP>Yamaha R15M is equipped with a quick shifter that allows gear changes without using the clutch or throttle.

common defect,maintenance issue	Honda Forza 350
Water Pump Leak
Honda Forza 350 may experience water pump leaks as a common defect in vehicles with high mileage.

common defect,user comfort issue	Seat Height
Yamaha XMAX 300
The seat height of Yamaha XMAX 300 poses a difficulty for shorter riders to reach the ground fully.

common defect,feature integration	GPX Drone 150
Keyless System
The Keyless System in GPX Drone 150 is prone to malfunctioning and finding signal issues.

common defect,maintenance issue	Honda Forza 350
Rear Mirror Vibration
Honda Forza 350 often faces rear mirror vibration as a common defect at higher speeds.

feature contrast,model comparison	MT-15
Yamaha XMAX 300
The MT-15 and Yamaha XMAX 300 are compared as different models with varying features like quick shifters and seat height.

common defect,maintenance issue	GPX Drone 150
Sensor Issues
The GPX Drone 150 experiences sensor issues with the side stand switch, leading to potential startup problems.

feature integration,user benefit	Ground Clearance
Honda Forza 350
The Honda Forza 350 has a ground clearance of 165 mm, which is higher than PCX and aids in better navigation over flooded areas or curbs.

feature integration,technology advancement	Y-Connect & Garmin Navigation
Yamaha XMAX 300
The Yamaha XMAX 300 Tech Max model integrates Y-Connect & Garmin Navigation for enhanced navigation capabilities.

engineering feature,performance enhancement	Showa
Technical Benefit
The technical benefit provided by Showa's sub-tank shock absorbers helps prevent cavitation during heavy use.

common defect,maintenance issue	Cooling System
GPX Drone 150
The cooling system in GPX Drone 150 faces issues with coolant leakage at hose clamp connections.

feature integration,user benefit	Honda Forza 350
Ride Height
The Honda Forza 350 has a ride height of 165 mm that aids in better navigation over flooded areas or curbs.

engineering advancement,product feature	Showa
Sub-Tank Shock Absorber
Showa produces sub-tank shock absorbers that help in separating oil and gas for better performance.

feature integration,user comfort	Honda Forza 350
Windscreen
The Honda Forza 350 features an adjustable windscreen that can be raised up to 180 mm.

engineering feature,performance enhancement	Cavitation Prevention
Showa
The Showa sub-tanks prevent cavitation by separating oil and gas in the rear shocks during heavy use.

engineering feature,performance enhancement	Dual Clamp Front Forks
Yamaha XMAX 300
The Yamaha XMAX 300 uses dual clamp front forks for improved handling and stability during high-performance maneuvers.

engineering advancement,product feature	Rear Shock Absorber
Showa
Showa provides rear shock absorbers with sub-tanks for enhanced performance.

feature integration,technological advancement	Tech Features
Yamaha R15M
The Yamaha R15M integrates various tech features such as the quick shifter and assist & slipper clutch for enhanced performance.

feature integration,technological advancement	TFT Display
Yamaha XMAX 300
The Yamaha XMAX 300 Tech Max model features a TFT display for enhanced navigation capabilities.

category inclusion,performance class	Honda Forza 350
Maxi-Sport
The Honda Forza 350 belongs to the category of maxi-scooters designed for long-distance touring.

engineering advancement,product feature	Showa
Suspension System
The suspension system benefits from Showa's rear shock absorbers with sub-tanks for better performance under heavy use.

category inclusion,performance class	Honda Forza 350
Touring Scooter
The Honda Forza 350 is categorized as a touring scooter designed for long-distance travel with comfort and power.

engineering feature,performance enhancement	Chassis Engineering
Yamaha XMAX 300
The chassis engineering in Yamaha XMAX 300 includes dual clamp front forks for improved stability and handling.

performance indicator,specification detail	Engine Specs
Honda Forza 350
The Honda Forza 350 has detailed engine specifications such as eSP+ 4 valves and a 329.6 cc displacement with the radiator moved to the front.

feature integration,technological advancement	Key Features
Yamaha XMAX 300
The Yamaha XMAX 300 features key elements such as the optional Y-Connect & Garmin Navigation for enhanced navigation capabilities.

component,functionality	Crankshaft
Roller Bearing
The crankshaft uses a roller bearing to reduce friction and vibration.

component comparison,similar technology	Piston Oil Jet
Wave 125i
A fuel jet under the piston is similar to that of Wave 125i.

performance metric,power output	Honda Forza 350
Performance Characteristics
The Honda Forza 350 has high torque output at low rpm levels, making it easier to accelerate and overtake other vehicles.

feature issue,maintenance concern	Common Defects
Yamaha XMAX 300
The Yamaha XMAX 300 experiences common defects including high oil consumption and a seat that may be difficult for shorter riders to use.

problem cause,solution	CVT Judder
Clutch Cloth Accumulation
Shaking during acceleration due to dust accumulation in the clutch housing can be resolved by cleaning or replacing the carbon clutch cloth.

material issue,resolution	Excessively Thick Oil
Oil Pump Gear Failure
Failure of the composite plastic oil pump gear may occur if excessively thick oil is used or sudden jerks are applied to the engine.

component,engine technology	VVA (Variable Valve Actuation)
Yamaha NMAX 155
Yamaha NMAX 155 uses the Blue Core VVA engine technology with variable valve actuation system.

component description,concern	Chassis
eSAF (Enhanced Smart Architecture Frame)
The lightweight chassis frame is made from stamped steel but has concerns about rust and long-term strength in some production lots.

feature integration,unique selling point	Honda Forza 350
Signature Feature
The Honda Forza 350 has an electric windshield that can be adjusted up to 180 mm as its signature feature.

component,strength improvement	Forged Piston
Yamaha NMAX 155
The Yamaha NMAX 155 features a forged piston similar to that used in R1 sports bikes for improved strength and reduced weight.

component,engine technology	Aerox 155
VVA (Variable Valve Actuation)
Aerox 155 also uses the Blue Core VVA engine technology with variable valve actuation system.

common defect,issue location	GPX Drone 150 (4-Valve)
Tensioner Failure
The chain tensioner in older models of GPX Drone 150 can fail and cause noisy operation.

feature,suspension technology	Honda ADV 160
Showa Suspension
The Honda ADV 160 uses rear suspension by Showa with a sub-tank to prevent cavitation when heavily used.

performance characteristic,power output	Honda Forza 350
Torque Master
The Honda Forza 350 is known as the Torque Master due to its ability to deliver high torque at low rpm levels for easy acceleration and overtaking.

comfort level,suspension type	Stiff Suspension
Yamaha NMAX 155
NMAX has a stiff rear suspension causing a rougher ride when driven solo.

defect,electrical issue	Aerox 155
Code 12 (Aerox/Lexi)
The Aerox model faces issues with the melting of stator coil terminals due to heat accumulation leading to poor electrical flow and starting problems.

collaboration partner,development relationship	GPX Drone 150 (4-Valve)
SYM
The GPX Drone 150 is developed in collaboration with SYM from Taiwan.

adjustability,component	Honda ADV 160
Windscreen
The Honda ADV 160 has an adjustable windscreen in two height levels.

performance enhancement,suspension	Honda Wave
Spiny Sleeve
The Spiny Sleeve helps improve grip and heat dissipation in Honda Wave motorcycles.

braking system,safety feature	Unified Brake System (UBS)
Yamaha Finn 115
The Yamaha Finn 115 is equipped with the Unified Brake System to enhance braking efficiency.

engine technology,performance enhancement	Honda PCX 160 & Click 160
Roller Bearing Crankshaft
Honda PCX 160 & Click 160 use roller bearing crankshafts to reduce friction and improve engine smoothness.

engineering spec,performance	Engine (147.3 cc DOHC 4 Valves)
Suzuki Raider R150
The Suzuki Raider R150 is equipped with a 147.3 cc DOHC 4 Valves engine for high performance.

functionality,vehicle feature	Ground Clearance
Honda ADV 160
The Honda ADV 160 has a ground clearance of 165 mm which allows it to perform better in flooded areas or on sidewalks compared to PCX.

fuel efficiency,marketing feature	Fuel Economy
Yamaha Finn 115
The Yamaha Finn 115 claims a fuel economy of 71.4 km/liter as part of its selling points.

engine technology,lubrication method	Honda PCX 160 & Click 160
Piston Oil Jet
Honda PCX 160 & Click 160 incorporate piston oil jet technology for efficient engine lubrication and performance.

frame design,structural strength	Suzuki Advanced Twin Spar Frame
Suzuki Raider R150
The Suzuki Raider R150 uses the Suzuki Advanced Twin Spar Frame to handle high torque effectively.

common defect,maintenance issue	Hard Shifting
Honda PCX 160 & Click 160
Honda PCX 160 & Click 160 are subject to hard shifting issues, especially in cold conditions.

navigation assistance,technology	TFT Screen
Tech Max
Tech Max is equipped with a full navigation map display on the TFT screen.

common defect,performance issue	Suzuki Raider R150
Vibration
The Suzuki Raider R150 experiences vibration that can be more pronounced as the engine ages.

engine type,performance feature	Kawasaki Ninja 400
Parallel Twin Engine
Kawasaki Ninja 400 is powered by a 399 cc parallel twin engine delivering 45 horsepower.

engineering feature,performance attribute	Four-Cylinder Engine
Kawasaki ZX-25R
Kawasaki ZX-25R is engineered with a 4-cylinder engine that reaches redline at 17,000 rpm.

storage capacity,utility feature	Honda Lead 125
U-Box Storage
Honda Lead 125 boasts the largest U-box storage in its class with a volume of 37 liters.

engine wear indicator,maintenance concern	Oil Consumption
Tech Max
Tech Max models have a common defect of high oil consumption, necessitating regular dipstick checks every 1,000 km to prevent engine damage due to lack of oil.

common defect,maintenance issue	CVT Judder
Honda PCX 160 & Click 160
Honda PCX 160 & Click 160 experience CVT judder, a shaking sensation while accelerating from 0-20 km/h.

efficiency enhancement,technology feature	Blue Core Hybrid Technology
Yamaha Grand Filano Hybrid
Yamaha Grand Filano Hybrid utilizes Blue Core Hybrid technology featuring an SMG motor to aid power delivery for smoother acceleration and better fuel economy.

high cost,maintenance requirement	Kawasaki Ninja 400
Major Service
Kawasaki Ninja 400 requires major service every 24,000 km with significant costs for valve setting, spark plug replacement, and fluid changes.

durability issue,maintenance concern	USD Fork Leak
Yamaha R15M
The Yamaha R15M has USD (Upside Down) forks that often suffer from sealant leaks if the fork shafts are hit by stones or debris.

ergonomics problem,user experience concern	Seat Height Issue
Tech Max
The seat height on Tech Max makes it challenging for shorter riders to place their feet flat on the ground when stationary.

high cost,maintenance concern	Kawasaki ZX-25R
Spark Plug Cost Issue
The Kawasaki ZX-25R requires expensive spark plugs for maintenance, costing between 400 to 600 baht each.

maintenance concern,reliability issue	Clutch Slippage Issue
Kawasaki Ninja 400
Kawasaki Ninja 400 models from 2018 to 2019 experienced clutch slippage due to weak clutch springs under heavy usage.

safety concern,user experience	Honda Lead 125
Wet Road Slippery Tires
The tires of the Honda Lead 125 become very slippery when encountering wet roads.

high cost,maintenance concern	Tire Cost Issue
Yamaha R15M
The rear tire of the Yamaha R15M is large at size 140/70-17 and is costly, ranging from 2,000 to 3,500 baht per piece.

common defect,maintenance issue	Honda PCX 160 & Click 160
Oil Pump Gear Failure
The Honda PCX 160 and Click 160 models have experienced oil pump gear failure due to the use of composite or plastic gears.

competitive positioning,market strategy	Honda Giorno+
Market Competition Against Grand Filano
The Honda Giorno+ is positioned in the market to compete directly with the Grand Filano and offers a more powerful engine.

high cost,maintenance concern	Kawasaki ZX-25R
Valve Clearance Maintenance Issue
The Kawasaki ZX-25R requires expensive labor for setting valve clearance due to the presence of 16 valves.

design flaw,user convenience issue	Honda Lead 125
Lack of Console Box
The Honda Lead 125 lacks a console box for additional storage and only provides a hanging hook.

performance enhancement,technology feature	Hybrid Motor Assistance
Yamaha Grand Filano Hybrid
The Yamaha Grand Filano Hybrid uses a Smart Motor Generator (SMG) for additional power assistance during the first 3 seconds of acceleration.

design flaw,user convenience issue	Honda Giorno+
Limited Storage Under Seat
The Honda Giorno+ has limited storage capacity under its seat compared to other models like Lead 125 and Grand Filano.
